Table S1: Experimental environment and execution constraints
Legend: Summary of the experimental environment and execution constraints used for all comparative runs. The table reports the Google Colab CPU-only platform configuration (OS, compute, memory, disk), software stack and library versions, and the fixed reproducibility settings (random seed, stratified 80/20 split, validation-based model selection). It also lists the matched wall-clock time budgets defining the Full (180 s) and Lightweight (60 s) regimes for AutoML, classical ML, and deep learning experiments.
Table S1: Experimental environment and execution constraints
Item	Specification
Execution platform	Google Colab (cloud notebook environment)
Operating system	Linux (kernel build: #1 SMP Thu Oct 2 10:42:05 UTC 2025)
CPU	2 vCPUs
GPU	Not available (CPU-only; CUDA not available)
Total RAM	12.67 GB
Available RAM at start (example run)	9.45 GB / 12.67 GB (74.6%)
Disk space available (example run)	85.00 GB / 107.72 GB (78.9%)
Python	3.12.12
AutoGluon	1.5.0
PyTorch	2.9.0+cpu
H2O AutoML	3.46.0.9
