Table S3: Metric definitions and computation details
Legend: Definitions of the predictive-performance and resource-efficiency metrics reported throughout the study, together with their exact computation procedures. The table specifies how classification metrics (Accuracy, ROC-AUC, F1-score, Precision, Recall, LogLoss, and confusion-matrix entries) are derived from model outputs (including the default probability threshold when applicable), and documents the measurement methodology for deployment-relevant costs—observed wall-clock runtime, process memory change (RSS), system-level memory utilization, and serialized model artifact size—ensuring consistent and reproducible reporting across ML, DL, and AutoML frameworks.
Table S3: Metric definitions and computation details
Category	Metric / Quantity	Definition	Computation / Implementation details
Predictive performance	Accuracy	Proportion of correct predictions.	Computed on the held-out test set using predicted labels.
Predictive performance	AUC (ROC-AUC)	Area under the ROC curve measuring ranking quality across thresholds.	Computed on the test set using predicted probabilities (positive class).
Predictive performance	F1-score	Harmonic mean of Precision and Recall.	Computed on the test set; binary F1 for the positive class (target=1).
Predictive performance	Precision	Fraction of predicted positives that are true positives.	Precision = TP / (TP + FP), computed on the test set.
Predictive performance	Recall (Sensitivity)	Fraction of true positives detected by the model.	Recall = TP / (TP + FN), computed on the test set.
Predictive performance	LogLoss	Penalizes miscalibrated probabilities via negative log-likelihood.	Computed on the test set from predicted probabilities (binary cross-entropy).
Predictive performance	Confusion matrix	Counts of TN, FP, FN, TP at a fixed threshold.	Threshold fixed at 0.5 unless the framework applies internal calibration; the resulting matrix is reported.
Runtime	Wall-clock runtime (s)	End-to-end elapsed time for training + selection under a budget.	Measured with time.time() as end_time - start_time around the entire fit/tuning routine for each run.
Runtime	Time budget policy	Defines “Full” vs “Lightweight” regimes.	Full = 180 s, Light = 60 s applied consistently across methods; some frameworks may show minor overhead beyond nominal limits.
Memory (process)	Python process RSS delta (MB)	Change in resident set size (RSS) of the Python process during training.	Measured via psutil.Process(os.getpid()).memory_info().rss; reported as end_rss - start_rss, converted to MB.
Memory (system)	System RAM usage delta (GB)	Change in overall system-used RAM during training.	Measured via OS-level memory snapshot (e.g., psutil.virtual_memory()); reported as end_used - start_used in GB.
Storage	Model file size (MB)	Disk footprint of the exported model artifact.	Measured via os.path.getsize(model_path) and converted to MB. For frameworks saving directories, the total directory size is used.
Reproducibility	Random seed	Controls split and training stochasticity where applicable.	Fixed seed (e.g., 42) used for data split and passed to methods that expose a seed/random_state parameter.
Evaluation protocol	Train/test split	Ensures unbiased performance reporting.	Stratified hold-out split with test_size=0.2; test set kept constant across all methods.
Evaluation protocol	Probability threshold	Converts probabilities to labels for confusion-matrix-based metrics.	Default threshold = 0.5 unless framework applies explicit decision-threshold calibration; reported metrics follow the final model output policy.

 
