Table S14. Friedman omnibus tests across repeated lightweight runs.
Legend: The table reports Friedman omnibus tests across five lightweight framework-level configurations evaluated on five repeated stratified 80/20 holdout splits. The compared methods were AutoGluon_Light, ClassicML_Light, FLAML_Light, H2O_Light, and MLJAR_Light. The Friedman test evaluates whether there is an overall difference among methods for each metric. A p-value below 0.05 was considered statistically significant. These results should be interpreted as exploratory robustness indicators; framework-level superiority should be assessed together with the pairwise Wilcoxon-Holm results in Table S13.
